title: Solar Orbiter Level 2 Phase Spase Distribution Function from Solar Wind Analyser (SWA) Proton-Alpha Sensor (PAS) - C.J. Owen (MSSL-UCL, University College London, UK)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/solar-orbiter/swa/science/l2/pas-vdf/2020/solo_l2_swa-pas-vdf_20200707_v02.cdf. The most common cadence occurred for 48.9452% of the 4849 timesteps. Cadence = 4000007000 [ns] = PT4.000007S.
info.contact: C.J. Owen @ MSSL-UCL, University College London, UK

parameters.name: Time
parameters.x_description: Epoch encoded as Terrestrial Time on rotating Earth geoid, ns since J2000

parameters.name: unrecovered_count
parameters.description: Total counter of unrecovered bins

parameters.description: Total count

parameters.name: quality_factor
parameters.description: Quality factor

parameters.name: vdf_mv
parameters.description: ---> Movie of above. This variable is a 'virtual' variable that is computed using the function alternate_view (see https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/pub/software/cdawlib/source/virtual_funcs.pro) on the with inputs of the variables ['vdf'].
